# Frontend Naming Conventions

- Use `snake_case` for frontend file and directory names by default.
- Preferred examples:
  - files: `token_store.ts`, `analytics_dashboard.stories.tsx`
  - directories: `auth_token`, `ui_components`
- Keep Remix route module filenames compatible with Remix routing requirements when needed.
- Keep route modules under `app/src/routes` in nested folders (for example `admin/gradings/results.tsx`), not dot-delimited filenames.
- For non-route source under `app/src`, always prefer `snake_case`.
- Keep symbol names descriptive and consistent with existing project style.
- When introducing new modules, match filename responsibility to exported symbol purpose.
